title: Spotify's Top 10 most viral tracks
text:
The Canadian Press - ONLINE EDITION Spotify's Top 10 most viral tracks By: The Associated Press Report Error 
The following list represents the most viral tracks on Spotify, based on the number of people who shared it divided by the number who listened to it, from Friday, Oct. 2, to Thursday, Oct. 8, via Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and Spotify. 
CANADA 
1. DNCE, "Cake by the Ocean" (Republic Records) 
2. B & Steve, "Home Run Anthem" (Wax Records) 
3. TroyBoi featuring Diplo and Nina Sky, "Afterhours" (Mad Decent) 
4. Louis the Child featuring K.Flay, "It's Strange" (Next Wave Records) 
5. GRADES, "King" (Warner Music UK Ltd.) 
6. Gnash featuring Olivia O'Brien, "I Hate U I Love U" (Gnash) 
7. Ruth B, "Lost Boy" (Columbia Records) 
8. Matt Simons, "Catch & Release (Deepend Remix)" (Republic Records) 
9. Bomba Estï¿½reo & Will Smith, "Fiesta (Remix)" (Sony Music Entertainment US Latin LLC)
